backstab^#^
SUBTOPIC-thief^#^
		-=[ Backstab ]=-

	Command: backstab
	Usage: backstab <who>

    Description: This command allows you to sneak up behind someone and
		 visciously strike them while they are not looking.

		 The common missunderstanding about backstab is that it
		 actually involves stabbing someone. This is incorrect.
		 Our own phrase 'stabbing someone in the back' comes from
		 the way in which a person can perform a task against
		 someone without them knowing about it. The same goes for
		 the backstab skill for thieves.

		 A backstab involves sneaking up behind someone, using
		 stealth, and SURPRISING them. This puts them off guard,
		 and puts a victim in a more vulnerable state. A thief 
		 knows how to do this with the upmost skill.

		 He then makes an attack upon his victim. It is the
		 gaining of surprise which is the key, not stabbing them.
		 Hence, the attack can be made with any weapon, be it
		 a stabbing weapon, a crushing weapon, or the like.

		 The unguarded state of the victim also means you can 
		 attack them in the nastiest of places, and hence do a
		 great deal of harm with a single blow. A strike to the
	         back of the neck, the head, the chest or from behind is
		 the usual method.


	Example: backstab bob

 Related Topics: move silently, hide in shadows.
